<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES - Fuel
        Injector O-Rings and Seals - Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="clean" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <figure id="f1200463" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg1/EG1073.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Fuel Injector O-Ring and Seal Locations</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Backup Ring (steel)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Upper Cushion Ring</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Upper O-Ring Seal</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Middle Seal</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Lower O-Ring Seal</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Copper Gasket</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>When installing the O-rings and seals onto the fuel injectors, make sure all O-rings and seals
                        are located at the top of the grooves to prevent them from rolling during installation.
                    </para>
                    <para>Also, make sure the O-rings and seals do not twist during installation.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Upper Groove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the upper groove seals.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lightly lubricate the new upper groove seal with clean engine oil.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The backup ring acts like a spring. Be careful when installing this part. Do not twist the
                        ring. Ring flatness is important.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Gently spread the gap in the backup ring. Slide the back up ring over the body of the
                    fuel injector and into the upper groove.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the cushion ring over the body of the fuel injector. Push the cushion ring into
                    the upper groove. Make sure the cushion ring is against the backup ring.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the O-ring over the body of the fuel injector and push it into the groove. Make
                    sure the O-ring is against the cushion ring.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Middle Groove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the middle groove seal.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lightly lubricate the seal with clean engine oil.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the middle seal over the fuel injector body and push into middle groove. Make sure
                    the middle fuel injector seal is against the groove.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Lower Groove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the lower groove seal.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lightly lubricate the seal with clean engine oil.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the lower seal over the fuel injector body and into the lower groove. Make sure
                    the lower fuel injector seal is against the groove.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply a light coat of grease to a new copper gasket. Place the gasket over the fuel
                    injector tip.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
